<br>
In order to get the movie made, Jackson et al needed to cut a few corners to hopefully encourage more than just the fanatics to see the movie.  Arwen isn't a bad means of doing it.  Dropping out some significant but not necessary scenes (Tom and others) is frustrating, but if the movie is 4 hours long, few would see it, and certainly not more than once.<br>
<br>
At present, I am still hopeful and don't condemn the choices made.  I wish they could have done it direct from the books, but then they'd have to make it twice as long and reduce th budget, and half the wonder of the visuals would be eliminated.<br>
